<head>FIX</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>MAKE PERMANENT</item>
<item>MAKE FAST</item>
<item>SET</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">確定</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">定</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>CAUSE something TO be ENDURING OR NOT to MOVE from a PLACE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for fixing something in any objective and interpersonal way, concrete or abstract is dìng 定.</p>
<p>2. Cái 裁 refers specifically to the proper apportioning of things.</p>
<p>3. Bì 必 refers to fixing and determining something with supreme assurance and definiteness.</p>
<p/>
<p>THIS IS A PRETTY MISERABLE GROUP: WHAT TO DO ABOUT IT?????</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>確定 focusses on the fixedness of the result.</p>
<p>決定 is the most current and general word for determining or fixing someting.</p>
<p>規定 focusses on the rules involved.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
    </div>
